description.narrative:
Summary This four-year project will strengthen the profile of the organisation by communicating the impact of the Commonwealth through vibrant external and internal communication, consistent branding, and impactful publications. In addition, the Communications Division makes use of on-line communication, social and mainstream media to reach key audiences with stories about the Commonwealth’s values, work, results and impact. It also maintains a Knowledge Centre that provides resources about the Commonwealth’s history and programmes.
COVID-19 pandemic has had a notable impact on the Secretariat's programmes and this will impact on how we deliver programmes in-country. Member states are grappling with the health, economic and social effect of the pandemic and now their focus has shifted to dealing with the crisis.
The project is designed to:
Ensure that the results of the Secretariat’s programmes and the values in the Commonwealth’s Charter are visible to key stakeholder groups and the informed public. The project will support all the intermediate outcomes of the Strategic Plan
ii. Communicate with key stakeholder groups and improved visibility of Commonwealth events and programmes contributes to all strategic outcome areas.
iii. Proactively promote strategic vision for the Commonwealth Secretariat to decrease focus on past issues.
iv. Increase visits to the Commonwealth’s website; improve coverage in mainstream media about the Commonwealth; and measure change in fans/followers of the Commonwealth’s social channels. Indicators will be tracked through production of a monthly visibility report.
v. Develop new ways of working and communicating with internal and external stakeholders during and after the crisis. As the Commonwealth, respond to the Comms team will continues to respond and engage in new ways and with new focuses with the media to promote the work we and the member states are undertaking.
vi. Create and implement a crisis communications plan that sets out clearly the steps to take and people and organisations to engage and coordinate with in the event of a crisis.
vii. Make visible our Knowledge Centre resources and publications
